column5: I managed to sneak away north on Saturday.  Smallies and largemouth were hitting on dropshot Gulp minnows, tubes and spinnerbaits at depths of 12-24 feet.  Attached is a typical smallie; sorry about the quality but it's the old phone while by yourself trick.
Nice Smallie.  Any leaves on the trees our are they close to bare yet?
was up there on the weekend too, the leaves are pretty well gone
Leaves are mostly gone up here....just the oaks hanging on now. Water temps are generaly mid 50s.
Great report. Sounds like you still have a few weeks more of bass fishing. I may have to wait till next year!
Thanks-it was great just to get out; the winds are starting to have a bit of bite to them though.  As for the leaves, yep, not too many left.  Cheers
